0.1 Perceived Intensity

For the intensity responses, we Fit a linear mixed-effects model (LMM) to data, via REML or maximum likelihood.we used lme4 R package [v1.1-33; @lme4].We regressed participants’ intensity for correct responses on these sets of regressors [intensity ∼ emotion * group * video_set + (1 |ID)] and computed significance levels for the fixed and random effects using the “anova” function, which returns a Type III ANOVA table with significance levels. We used Phia R package [v0.2-1; Rosario-Martinez (2015)].
